author: @onlyme112
text: I love this movie.  It instantly became one of my favorites when the F-35's escorted Santa back to the North Pole.  The movie brought out the 8-year-old boy in me, while also providing a plausible explanation for how Santa can visit every house on earth in one night.  My only regret is with Dwayne Johnson's acting -- I don't know why he played his part so stiffly.  I want to give him the benefit of the doubt and say that he was told to act that way, but then again, I haven't seen him in other movies.  He seemed to be rushing through some of his lines.  Anyway, I'm already on my second run-through of this movie and look forward to revisiting it again next year.  Kavalame!
